  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [x] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (5916d38 2022-03-30T16:31:01.267891+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (M1)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\ntx.gasprice is always set to 0. This is the case even when gas_price parameter in foundry.toml is set to non-zero value.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"510\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13470840/160888967-8a4c90fe-7679-41d5-a7e4-c00075fedc74.png\">\r\n\r\n`function testDisplayBaseFeeAndGasPrice() public {\r\n        emit log_uint(block.basefee);\r\n        emit log_uint(tx.gasprice);\r\n    }`",
